Certainly! To calculate the mean (average) value of four integers using JavaScript, you can sum up the integers and then divide by the number of integers. Here's a simple JavaScript code snippet to achieve that:

```javascript
// Define the integers
let num1 = 6;
let num2 = 2;
let num3 = 10;
let num4 = 12;

// Calculate the sum of the integers
let sum = num1 + num2 + num3 + num4;

// Calculate the mean by dividing the sum by the number of integers
let mean = sum / 4;

// Output the result
console.log("The mean value is: " + mean);
```

When you run this code, it will calculate the mean of the integers 6, 2, 10, and 12, and then output the result. In this case, the mean value will be 7.5.
